            <div class="sectionHeaderClass" style="font-weight:bold;">WISCONSIN STATE PATIENTCOMPENSATION FUND:</div>
            If you are scheduled to provide professional services in the state of Wisconsin, all assignment dates will be reported to the Wisconsin state patient’s compensation fund. The fund will send an invoice/exemption form to your home address and it is your sole responsibility to either bind coverage with the fund by paying the invoice accordingly or claim an exemption. You may view the list of exemption factors by accessing the following link (http://oci.wi.gov/pcf.htm) and clicking on exemptions from fund coverage. Please note that fund participation is mandatory if you do not qualify for an exemption and failure to comply with the fund may result in actions being taken against your Wisconsin state medical license.
